/*
This gem is to remove any duplicates from the pipeline. 

Some duplicates arose (as expected) because of the method of doing 2 joins and the union; in examples where the source system 
had the conversion ~ "both ways" e.g. EA --> CA = 12 AND CA --> EA = 0.0833.

In this situation I wanted to keep the 12 EA in a CA rather than an EA is 0.0833 of case. 
I managed this via the JOIN_ORIGIN being a number: 1 where the BASE_UOM = UMUM meaning the UMRUM (related) is the ALT. This
ensures that when both calculations exist, we only take the one that says that the ALT_UOM is x number of BASE_UOMs 
and not a BASE_UOM is 0.8 number of ALTs

There are examples about 30 out of 1 million (0.003%) where there is ONLY the ALT = 0.0833 of the BASE but that is the only data
there is so we have to go with it.

This row_num also takes care of the duplicates on JSW although it does mean that the values brought in are for a ~ random plant 

 */

SELECT 
    *
FROM 
    (SELECT
        in0.*,
        row_number() OVER(PARTITION BY ITEM, ALT_UOM ORDER BY ITEM, ALT_UOM, JOIN_ORIGIN) row_num
    FROM
        in0) a
WHERE row_num = 1
